---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Joshua Bisdorf.">
  <section class="page-hero container">
    <h1>About Me</h1>
    <p>
      Software Engineer at KBR, M.S. Computer Science student at UT Austin, and University of
      Michigan Computer Science graduate, magna cum laude.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-photo-strip container" aria-label="Photos of Joshua Bisdorf">
    <figure>
      <img
        src="/images/joshua-arizona.jpg"
        alt="Joshua Bisdorf standing in the Arizona desert"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <figcaption>Arizona</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <figure>
      <img
        src="/images/joshua-bjj.jpg"
        alt="Joshua Bisdorf at a Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu tournament"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <figcaption>Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--bordered">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 760px; display: grid; gap: 1.5rem;">
      <p>
        I’m a Software Engineer at KBR, where I work on radar software supporting defense and
        intelligence systems. Alongside my professional work, I’m pursuing an M.S. in Computer
        Science at The University of Texas at Austin while working full-time in Ann Arbor, Michigan.
      </p>

      <p>
        I earned my B.S.E. in Computer Science from the University of Michigan, graduating magna cum
        laude, and have developed strong interests in artificial intelligence and machine learning,
        cybersecurity, network security, and computer vision. I’m particularly interested in the
        intersection of AI/ML and cloud computing, especially cloud-native AI systems and the
        security of AI systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        My technical background and interests include C++, Python, Linux, Docker, networking, cloud
        computing, cybersecurity, and machine learning systems. I enjoy working on problems that sit
        at the intersection of software engineering, infrastructure, and intelligent systems.
      </p>

      <!-- <p>
        I chose UT Austin for two reasons: the flexibility to continue advancing my education while
        working full-time, and the opportunity to deepen my connection to a region I hope to call
        home someday. I’m especially interested in relocating to Texas, particularly the Austin
        area, given its strong technology presence and alignment with my interests.
      </p> -->

      <p>
        Outside of work and school, I train Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu and have a particular interest in
        no-gi training, a natural extension of my decade-long wrestling background growing up.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
